Install mathkaba, run

  ./configure
  make
  make install

Additional command line parameters can be given to configure, such as

  --prefix=PREFIX : sets the installation prefix
  --enable-debug  : configure with debugging options

Environement variables like CXXFLAGS and CPPFLAGS may also be useful.

Cross-compilation for MS Windows using mingw32
----------------------------------------------

If you are using mingw32 to perform a cross-compilation towards MS
Windows, a typical ./configure invocation may look like:

  ./configure --host=i486-mingw32
